title: Rick's Pick 6
text:
No. 11 Pennsbury at No. 15 Pennridge. The Falcons and Rams both feature run-heavy attacks. Pennsbury rolled to a 41-14 victory last season. Pick: Pennsbury, 26-20. 

Episcopal Academy at No. 6 Malvern Prep. The Churchmen and Friars have breakaway threats in Dee Barlee and O'Shaan Allison, respectively. Pick: Malvern, 27-13. 

Conestoga at Marple Newtown. How about those 6-0 Tigers? Red-hot Marple is bidding for its first Central League championship since 1977. Pick: Marple, 23-21. 

Germantown Academy at Springside Chestnut Hill. The undefeated Patriots have a strong pass-catch duo in Kyle McCloskey and James McAfee. Pick: GA, 28-27.
